The chairman of the professional association of practical pediatricians, Hana Cabrnochova, admits that voluntary vaccination has its disadvantages.
“In a situation where the vaccine is so expensive, we understand the political decision that this vaccination was launched as voluntary,” says Dr. Cabrnochova.
Experts expect more than 80 percent of parents to get their babies vaccinated against pneumococci from next year.
