Pakistani authorities uncovered a supposed leader of a conspiracy aimed at sending five men from Northern Virginia to Afghanistan to kill U.S. soldiers on Saturday, saying they hoped this case could help uncover an extensive network of terrorist recruiters searching the internet for radicalized young men.
Investigators said they had sought an oppressive rebel, known as Saifullah, who had invited the men to Pakistan after searching for them because one of them had submitted approving comments on terrorist attacks on the Internet video site YouTube.
