High-level officials, such as Indian Environment Minister Jairam Ramesh and Chinese Deputy Prime Minister, took off their planes and rushed through the Bella Center corridors to meetings behind closed doors and press conferences to cover claims that will be negotiated over the next week.
The pure scale of the assembly -- 13,000 people enter and exit the congress centre every day, guitar-playing activists host night shows where they make fun of the countries they think are betraying and selling, and draft contracts are hand-to-hand instead of e-mailed -- is already a challenge.
