The purpose of this purchase was to offer its customers more services and value-added, with the opportunity to gain access to a huge international market.
This assessment and purchase service is exclusively aimed at industry professionals, such as insurance companies, assessors, car rental companies, workshops, garbage sites and car dealers who need to register before their activities.
Established in 1996 in Germany, this platform manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of which in Germany alone.
Its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
Today, the site has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 reviewers.
Every day, 3,000 ads are managed and 100 new ads are added to the Spanish market every day.
According to Spanish legislation, a vehicle whose passenger number has been registered can no longer drive on the roads, but certain undamaged parts may be used as spare parts.
Cars of historical value, on the other hand, can be re-registered even if they have been discharged after difficult administrative procedures.
Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: Identifying the vehicle, finding the spare part, creating and creating a cost estimate.
The ease of handling these systems is a basic condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 small vehicles and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an Internet connection.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graph of the respective model will appear and then the necessary spare part will be selected.
The user can include variables, such as the price for working hours, surcharges or discounts, and then they can print the cost estimate and pass it on to their customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a review tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can pay without further delay.
Currently, Audatex is working to offer these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that automotive mechanics have been waiting for for a long time, as it allows you to select a door, for example, and then turn the picture completely around to look at the inside.
